Privacy Policy for Q-Invoice Lite

This privacy policy governs your use of the software application Q-Invoice Lite (“Application”) for mobile devices.

1. What information does the Application obtain and how is it used?

The Application does not require any registration and does not collect any personal data from its users. All the information related to business name, currency preference, invoice header and footer text, and other transaction-related information are stored locally on your device and are not collected or used by us.

2. Does the Application collect precise real-time location information of the device?

This Application does not collect precise information about the location of your mobile device.

3. Do third parties see and/or have access to information obtained by the Application?

No personal data is collected, therefore, no third parties have access to personal information obtained by the Application.

4. Advertisements

The Application uses third-party advertising companies to serve ads when you use our mobile app. These companies may use information about your use of our services in order to provide advertisements about goods and services of interest to you.

5. Changes

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time for any reason. We will notify you of any changes to our Privacy Policy by posting the new Privacy Policy here. You are advised to consult this Privacy Policy regularly for any changes.

6. Your Consent

By using the Application, you are consenting to our processing of your information as set forth in this Privacy Policy now and as amended by us.

7. Contact us

If you have any questions regarding privacy while using the Application, or have questions about our practices, please contact us via email at support@msolutions.lk.

